cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC 

This paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper specifically discusses the capacity of a multiple access channel, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). The paper also discusses cognitive networks, which are a subset of communication networks and are typically categorized under cs.SI (social and information networks). The paper may also fall under cs.MM (multimedia) as it deals with transmitting multiple messages simultaneously. Finally, the paper may be categorized under cs.CC (computational complexity) as it discusses the complexity of determining the capacity of the multiple access channel.
